The front grille of the Jeep Grand Cherokee in the image is a prominent feature that helps identify the model. In terms of shape and size, the grille spans a significant portion of the front fascia, covering the upper half of the bumper area. It is rectangular in overall shape, with the top edge being slightly curved to match the hood's contour. The grille also includes integrated fog light housings on either side, which are seamlessly integrated into the design without compromising its clean lines.
